templete-vim
============

template chooser for vim

Usage:
------

Open new file

```sh
# vim foo.pl
```

```vim
:Template <tab>
```

Then you can select `package` or `script` for perl filetype.

```vim
:Template package
:Template script
```

Type <enter> in 'script', you can see following.

```perl
use strict;
use warnings
use utf8;

|
```

And cursor is in `|`. If you open C++ file, you can select `main` for C.

